snippet.textDisplay:
Hello! 👋 I'm here to tell you not to overfill your piping bag.
If you hold the bag in your hand and fold the top 2-3 inches inside out so it cups over the back of your hand, it's easier to hold onto, you'll make less of a mess, you can scrape it off the spatula using your hand and it'll go into the bag, and you will make sure you don't overfill it 👍
snippet.textOriginal:

Btw, when you fill a piping bag, you gotta leave around a free inch at the top (it's easier to fill it putting it in a glass and folding that inch over the glass top) so when you finish you undo the fold and twist the free top. snippet.textDisplay: I might be taking your question when you asked, 'What's been going on with you guys?' too seriously, but for some reason my gut told me to respond. Honestly, life has been a little bit rocky. My son got diagnosed with mild Autism (Asperger's)/Anxiety/& ADHD back in August of 2019 and I have been trying to get his medications, etc. in order along with educating myself/learning how to better help my son all while being a single mom who has an awesome boyfriend who is trying their best to help, but learning along with me.. I've been really stressed because I was anticipating on getting more money back come tax time than what I am going to be getting back and I just feel like I'm wearing thin. I know it's just a rough patch, and I guess I needed somewhere to vent. Sorry this is a lot.
